arts.ttl: Leeds United 2-2 Bournemouth: Late equaliser leaves the Whites lost for words
arts.sum: Leeds fought back with Joe Rodon powering home a header from a Sean Longstaff cross to level the score before the break. Leeds, unchanged from last weekend's win at Wolves, started well and could have perhaps been ahead, but Dominic Calvert-Lewin, fresh from his goal last week, could only find the gloves of Djordje Petrovic.

arts.ttl: Leeds United 2-2 Bournemouth: Post Match Leeds United Player Ratings
arts.sum: Leeds United were denied all three points in heartbreaking fashion at Elland Road as Bournemouth snatched a stoppage-time equaliser to force a 2-2 draw. Not the most polished display in possession from the Leeds stalwart, with a few tentative moments when pressed, but defended the box with determination.
